title: Untitled (Five Pointe O album)
text:
Untitled is the only album from the <a href="nu%20metal">nu metal</a> band <a href="Five%20Pointe%20O">Five Pointe O</a>. The album was released on March 19, 2002 via <a href="Roadrunner%20Records">Roadrunner Records</a>.
Background.
The album's only single, "Double X Minus", received airplay on <a href="MTV2">MTV2</a>'s <a href="Headbangers%20Ball">Headbangers Ball</a> and <a href="Kerrang%21%20TV">Kerrang! TV</a>. "The Infinity" was featured on the "<a href="Resident%20Evil%20%282002%20film%29">Resident Evil</a>" soundtrack.
Reception.
"<a href="Exclaim%21">Exclaim!</a>" compared the album favorably to the early music of <a href="Linkin%20Park">Linkin Park</a>.
